<recipe>
<title>
Homemade Kansas City Style Barbecue Sauce
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 10 minutes
COOK TIME: 40 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 50 minutes
COURSE: Sauce
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: sauce
SERVINGS: 24
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="0.3333333333333333 Cup">Molasses</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.3333333333333333 Cup">Sugar</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.3333333333333333 Cup">Apple</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 Teaspoon">Garlic</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5 Teaspoon">Paprika</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5 Teaspoon">Mus</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5 Teaspoon">Chili Powder</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5 Teaspoon">Onion Powder</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5 Teaspoon">Pepper</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
In a medium saucepan, stir together all of the ingredients except liquid smoke.
Bring to boil over medium-low heat, whisking regularly.
Once at a boil, reduce heat to low, and let simmer 30 minutes, stirring regularly. 
Stir in liquid smoke to taste.
Let cool to room temperature.
Transfer to a container, and store, covered, in the fridge for up to 1 month.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>